# Scope discipline (read this carefully)
- Modify ONLY the exact lines required to satisfy the spec. Nothing else.
- Do NOT add usage of newly-introduced fields, classes, or functions elsewhere in the file — that is a SEPARATE work package and is OUT OF SCOPE here.
- Do NOT modify functions, classes, or comments that the spec did not name. Even if you see a "better way," it is out of scope.
- Do NOT add imports unless the spec requires a new dependency.
- Do NOT add docstrings or comments beyond what the spec specifies.
- If you find the transformation already done, output an empty diff:
    --- a/<path>
    +++ b/<path>
  with no hunks. Validation will catch the empty hunks and the Dev Orchestrator will mark this WP as already-applied.
- Speculative "helpful" additions are the most common failure mode for tier-1 work. Resist them.

